HEADWORD: Exsiccant
<hw>Ex*sic"cant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exsiccans</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>exsiccare</ets>. See
<er>Exsiccate</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the quality of drying up; causing
a drying up.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An
exsiccant medicine.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

